verses.text:
Then sang Moses and the children of Israel this song unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, and spake , saying , I will sing unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, for he hath triumphed gloriously : the horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea.

The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* my strength and song , and he is become my salvation : he \add is\add* my God , and I will prepare him an habitation ; my father’s God , and I will exalt him.

The 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* a man of war : the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* his name.
Pharaoh’s chariots and his host hath he cast into the sea : his chosen captains also are drowned in the Red sea.
The depths have covered them: they sank into the bottom as a stone.

Thy right hand , O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, is become glorious in power : thy right hand , O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, hath dashed in pieces the enemy.
And in the greatness of thine excellency thou hast overthrown them that rose up against thee: thou sentest forth thy wrath , \add which\add* consumed them as stubble.
And with the blast of thy nostrils the waters were gathered together , the floods stood upright as an heap , \add and\add* the depths were congealed in the heart of the sea.

The enemy said , I will pursue , I will overtake , I will divide the spoil ; my lust shall be satisfied upon them; I will draw my sword , my hand shall destroy them.\f + \fr 15.9 \ft destroy: or, repossess\f*
Thou didst blow with thy wind , the sea covered them: they sank as lead in the mighty waters.

Who \add is\add* like unto thee, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, among the gods ? who \add is\add* like thee, glorious in holiness , fearful \add in\add* praises , doing wonders ?\f + \fr 15.11 \ft gods: or, mighty ones?\f*
Thou stretchedst out thy right hand , the earth swallowed them.
Thou in thy mercy hast led forth the people \add \+w which|strong="H2098"\+w*\add* thou hast redeemed : thou hast guided \add them\add* in thy strength unto thy holy habitation.
The people shall hear , \add and\add* be afraid : sorrow shall take hold on the inhabitants of Palestina.
Then the dukes of Edom shall be amazed ; the mighty men of Moab , trembling shall take hold upon them; all the inhabitants of Canaan shall melt away.

Fear and dread shall fall upon them; by the greatness of thine arm they shall be \add as\add* still as a stone ; till thy people pass over , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, till the people pass over , \add \+w which|strong="H2098"\+w*\add* thou hast purchased.

Thou shalt bring them in, and plant them in the mountain of thine inheritance , \add in\add* the place , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, \add which\add* thou hast made for thee to dwell in , \add in\add* the Sanctuary , O Lord , \add which\add* thy hands have established.
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* shall reign for ever and ever.

For the horse of Pharaoh went in with his chariots and with his horsemen into the sea , and the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* brought again the waters of the sea upon them; but the children of Israel went on dry \add land\add* in the midst of the sea. \p
¶ And Miriam the prophetess , the sister of Aaron , took a timbrel in her hand ; and all the women went out after her with timbrels and with dances.
And Miriam answered them, Sing ye to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, for he hath triumphed gloriously ; the horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea. \p
So Moses brought Israel from the Red sea , and they went out into the wilderness of Shur ; and they went three days in the wilderness , and found no water. \p

¶ And when they came to Marah , they could not drink of the waters of Marah , for they \add were\add* bitter : therefore the name of it was called Marah.\f + \fr 15.23 \ft Marah: that is Bitterness\f*
And the people murmured against Moses , saying , What shall we drink ?

And he cried unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*; and the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* shewed him a tree , \add which\add* when he had cast into the waters , the waters were made sweet : there he made for them a statute and an ordinance , and there he proved them,

And said , If thou wilt diligently hearken to the voice of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God , and wilt do that which is right in his sight , and wilt give ear to his commandments , and keep all his statutes , I will put none of these diseases upon thee, which I have brought upon the Egyptians : for I \add am\add* the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* that healeth thee. \p
¶ And they came to Elim , where \add were\add* twelve wells of water , and threescore and ten palm trees : and they encamped there by the waters.
